More and more often I started noticing the solutions like 

```
testNumber = 0;
var fakeSolution = function(params) {
  return [15, 1432, 5234, ... ][testNumber++];  
};
```

First of all, what is the point to submit this kind of solutions? In the end, as I understand, this platform is about studying and self improvement, by "faking" solution people just fool themselves 🤷‍♂️
Secondly, it is just so easy to avoid this kind of solutions by creating randomised tests, this is quite weird to me that platforms like this do not have this approach as a requirement 😕
